A couple was found dead with gunshot wounds at their rented room in Hambanathi, Tongaat, in northern KwaZulu-Natal on Monday morning. According to the Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA), the couple was found dead on the floor with gunshot wounds to their heads. A 9mm pistol was found laying between them. The man died at the scene while the woman died at hospital shortly after arrival. Spokesperson for RUSA, Prem Balram, said their officers and police were informed that the woman was heard screaming before shots were fired. Police are yet to comment on the matter.